college_profile.typical_earning_for_college_details_page: Graduates earn about $38K at the median a decade after enrolling (Scorecard).
college_profile.campus_diversity: Hispanic-Serving commuter college with majority Hispanic/Latine enrollment and sizeable non-traditional student population.
college_profile.test_score: Open admission; placement uses Accuplacer/Guided Self-Placement, not SAT/ACT.
college_profile.food: Food costs are folded into the $18,540 off-campus allowance; typical student grocery/meal plan budgets run $3,500-$4,000/year.
college_profile.crime_rate: Clery reports show low incident counts typical of a commuter campus; no residential housing.
college_profile.salary_range: $17K–$57K earnings range (25th–75th percentile 10 years after entry)
college_profile.faculty_with_phd: Most faculty hold master’s or terminal credentials; full-time faculty share is about 22%.
college_profile.rank: High licensure-pass alignment with NM Board of Nursing standards for ADN graduates.
college_profile.academic_excellence: Concept-based curriculum with integrated pharmacology, simulation, and clinical rotations across northern New Mexico hospitals.
college_profile.facilities: Simulation labs, skills labs, and on-campus clinical practice rooms.
college_profile.student_life: Cohort model with peer tutoring, NCLEX prep workshops, and Student Nurses Association involvement.
